{
  "stem": "6526.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We remained under German rule.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was in 1939, the end of September when we came back.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Much more difficult became when they started to prepare for against-- well, actually I cannot describe when it came, because it was always difficult.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As we say it in Yiddish, yesterday was a good day, because every day that was, was a bad day.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yesterday was a good day.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When my father was selected for one of the Judenrat, there was a lot of people, wealthy people and known people, good senior citizens of the town, known all over, and my father was known all over.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they start to see-- start to discuss, how can we break the German will?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They should not punish us so much.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The only way to do it is buy them off.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they decided, each one of Judenrat had a mission, and whether my father volunteered to it or was appointed, that they should be going to the Germans and negotiate with them.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But this was thought about.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But before this happened, the Germans themselves, when they came over to town, our house was the first house-- Jewish house-- and they came in right away there.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they saw this, we want this, we want that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They started to beat and this and that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And came to a position that my father got friendly with them-- friendly with them, and they said, you need something, you have a wife, you need a ring, and started to buy them off.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it started, whatever it came a law, where the Jews to go here or not to go there, used to be flatten it down.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Instead of 100%, used to be 80% and less and less.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And this is how we lived.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
